@Jamie 

I watched hundreds of VHS tapes over some 15 or 20 years, many of them borrowed, of various qualities (in the early 90s all VHS rental places only had pirated copies of everything as we still did not have modern copyright laws back then) and I experienced none of issues you describe. Could it be about the US video standard at the time being NTSC and the European one PAL/SECAM? I remember especially our first, 1980s VCR very well, a Philips, and I'm 99% sure it had no knobs, at all, and the buttons were only FF, RW, Play, Pause, Stop and Record.

@HeathieJ

